    • canSkipAnimation

      public boolean canSkipAnimation()
      Checks if this door can be opened instantly (i.e. skip the animation).

      This describes whether skipping the animation actually does anything. When a door can skip its animation, it means that the actual toggle has an effect on the world and as such toggling it without an animation does something.

      Doors that do not have any effect other than their animation because all their blocks start and stop at exactly the same place (i.e. flags) cannot skip their animation because skipping the animation would mean removing the blocks of the door from their locations and then placing them back at exactly the same position. This would be a waste of performance for both the server and the client and as such should be prevented.

      Returns:
      True, if the door can skip its animation.

    • cycleOpenDirection

      public RotateDirection cycleOpenDirection()
      Cycle the RotateDirection direction this IDoor will open in. By default, it'll set and return the opposite direction of the current direction.

      Note that this does not actually change the open direction; it merely tells you which direction comes next!

      Returns:
      The new RotateDirection direction this IDoor will open in.

    • constructBlockMover

      protected abstract BlockMover constructBlockMover(BlockMover.Context context, DoorActionCause cause, double time, boolean skipAnimation, Cuboid newCuboid, IPPlayer responsible, DoorActionType actionType) throws Exception
      Gets the Supplier for the BlockMover for doorBase type.

      doorBase method MUST BE CALLED FROM THE MAIN THREAD! (Because of MC, spawning entities needs to happen synchronously)

      Parameters:
      cause - What caused doorBase action.
      time - The amount of time doorBase DoorBase will try to use to move. The maximum speed is limited, so at a certain point lower values will not increase door speed.
      skipAnimation - If the DoorBase should be opened instantly (i.e. skip animation) or not.
      newCuboid - The Cuboid representing the area the door will take up after the toggle.
      responsible - The IPPlayer responsible for the door action.
      actionType - The type of action that will be performed by the BlockMover.
      context - The BlockMover.Context to run the block mover in.
      Returns:
      The BlockMover for doorBase class.
      Throws:
      Exception
